<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p>Common questions about residential electrical services in Utah.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How do I know if my home needs rewiring?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Common signs include frequently tripped breakers, flickering lights, discolored or warm outlets, a burning smell near switches, two-prong outlets throughout the home, or a house built before 1970 that has never been rewired. Osborne Electric offers free safety assessments to evaluate your wiring and provide honest recommendations.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How much does it cost to install a new outlet in Utah?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>A standard outlet installation typically ranges from $150 to $350 depending on the location in your home, wiring complexity, and whether new circuit wiring is needed. GFCI outlets for kitchens, bathrooms, and outdoor areas may cost slightly more due to the specialized hardware. Call <a href="tel:801-885-4521">801-885-4521</a> for a free estimate tailored to your specific situation.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Do I need a permit for residential electrical work in Utah?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>In Utah, permits are required for most electrical work beyond simple fixture replacements. This includes adding new circuits, rewiring, <a href="/services/panel-upgrades/">panel upgrades</a>, and adding outlets. Osborne Electric handles all permit applications and scheduling of inspections so you do not have to worry about the paperwork.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How often should I have my home's electrical system inspected?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>We recommend a professional electrical inspection every 3 to 5 years for most homes, or immediately when purchasing an older home. Homes over 40 years old, or those experiencing frequent breaker trips, flickering lights, or other anomalies, should be inspected right away. Osborne Electric provides thorough safety inspections across all five counties we serve.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

